					<description><!--[CDATA[<p-->In Lusaka, Zambia, where clinical improvisation is often essential, Mayo Clinic anesthesiologist Kashmira Chawla, M.D., led a group of senior residents from&nbsp;Mayo Clinic School of Graduate Medical Education&nbsp;(MCSGME) on a collaborative expedition to improve airway management and perioperative care.&nbsp; Supported by a scholarship from the Mayo Clinic Global Health Program, Dr. Chawla and her trainees […]<p></p>
